comments.body:
@Luap99 So the concern here is that `host.containers.internal` normally does not point to localhost, so we get different behavior after this change for host network vs non-host network?

I see the concern, but I'm honestly not that worried... Host networking is already significantly different from bridge networking. I don't think a further change in `host.containers.internal` will be that noticeable?

(That aside, I definitely agree with the refactoring suggestion, let's keep this in the existing function to generate the alias)

@kairosci No like I said we are already working on the vendoring issues, the buildah side is already fixed via https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/6650

I suggest you stop pushing (random?) changes here that have nothing to do with your actual change. You should not do any of such CI system changes here, if you found bugs please report them (and once we confirm them) you can fix them in other PRs but otherwise please do not blindly change this stuff, doing runtime installs of packages are simply not acceptable in our CI systems.
For now a PR like this is just not reviewable anymore.
